The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Congress of the United States. In the letter, President Biden designates all funding designated by Congress in the Emergency Security Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2021 as emergency requirements. This designation is in accordance with section 606 of the Act and section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The specific details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Acting Director of the Office of Management and Budget. The letter is dated July 30, 2021, and comes from the White House.